definitions.definition: To agree ; to be equal ; to correspond .
examples: Their interests didn't match , so it took a long time to agree what to do together.
These two copies are supposed to be identical, but they don't match .

definitions.definition: To agree with; to be equal to; to correspond to.
examples: His interests didn't match her interests.

definitions.definition: To equal or exceed in achievement .
examples: She matched him at every turn: anything he could do, she could do as well or better.

definitions.definition: To make a successful match or pairing .
examples: They found out about his color-blindness when he couldn't match socks properly.

definitions.definition: To unite in marriage, to mate.
To fit together, or make suitable for fitting together; specifically, to furnish with a tongue and groove at the edges.
To be an example of a rule or regex .
examples: The behavior matched one or more rules and was rejected by an edit filter.

main_definition: ( intransitive ) To agree ; to be equal ; to correspond .
secondary_definitions: ( transitive ) To agree with; to be equal to; to correspond to.
( transitive ) To equal or exceed in achievement .
( transitive ) To make a successful match or pairing .
( obsolete ) To unite in marriage, to mate.
To fit together, or make suitable for fitting together; specifically, to furnish with a tongue and groove at the edges.
( transitive , programming ) To be an example of a rule or regex .
